# UI / web formatting

All indentation, line endings, charset, trimming, and per-type line length are defined in the repository root **[`.editorconfig`](../../.editorconfig)**. Editors that support EditorConfig apply it automatically.

**Web stack in this repo (see sections “Web assets” and `*.svg` in `.editorconfig`):**

- **Indent:** 2 spaces for HTML, CSS, JS/TS, and SVG (common for front-end tooling and readable nested markup).
- **Line length:** 120 characters for those types (tighter than Java’s 160 — better for templates and side‑by‑side review).
- **Charset / EOL:** UTF-8 and LF with a final newline (global `[*]` defaults).

When generating or editing Thymeleaf, static assets, or small SVGs, match `.editorconfig` so diffs stay consistent with the rest of the UI work. For template and stack conventions, see **`ui-templates.mdc`** and **`ui-guardrails.mdc`**.
